# PHC — Naming & Architecture Conventions

PHC is a frontend-only mock app (no backend, no Web3). All data is in `src/lib/mockData.ts` and Zustand stores under `src/lib/stores/`.

## Roles

Two roles only — **clipper** and **brand**. The Zustand auth store lives in `src/lib/stores/authStore.ts`. Role-gated areas are:

- `src/pages/clipper/**` → `/clipper/*` routes (rendered inside `src/layouts/ClipperLayout.tsx`)
- `src/pages/brand/**` → `/brand/*` routes (rendered inside `src/layouts/BrandLayout.tsx`)
- `src/pages/auth/AuthPage.tsx` → `/auth`
- `src/pages/onboarding/RoleSelectionPage.tsx` → `/onboarding/role`

The single `src/components/layout/AppSidebar.tsx` handles both roles via a `role` prop.

## Files

### Components & pages

- **PascalCase** `.tsx`: `CampaignCard.tsx`, `AppSidebar.tsx`, `ClipperLayout.tsx`
- **Exception:** files under `src/components/ui/` follow shadcn defaults (lowercase, e.g. `button.tsx`, `dropdown-menu.tsx`)

### Page colocation

Each page lives in its own folder when it has multiple sub-files. Otherwise a single `*Page.tsx` is fine. Examples that already exist:

- `src/pages/clipper/dashboard/DashboardPage.tsx`
- `src/pages/brand/campaigns/CreateCampaignPage.tsx`

### Hooks

- File name: kebab-case after `use-`: `useAuth.ts` (this codebase keeps simple `useAuth.ts` style under `src/lib/hooks/`)
- Exported hook: camelCase with `use` prefix.

### Stores (Zustand)

- camelCase, suffixed with `Store`: `authStore.ts`, `clipsStore.ts`, `campaignsStore.ts`, `paymentMethodsStore.ts`
- Location: `src/lib/stores/`

### Utilities

- camelCase: `cn.ts`, `currency.ts`, `date.ts`
- Location: `src/lib/utils/`

### Mock data

- All seed data lives in `src/lib/mockData.ts`. Stores import from there.

## Folders

- Lowercase or kebab-case: `clipper`, `brand`, `campaigns`, `bug-submission-details` (avoid in PHC).

## Branding

- Primary brand: **PHC — Philippine Clippers**
- Color system uses `--primary` (violet), `--accent` (pink), and the PHC gradient utility classes:
  - `bg-phc-gradient` — full violet → pink → orange
  - `text-phc-gradient` — same gradient as text
  - `bg-phc-gradient-soft` — subtle tinted background
- Display font: `Sora` (use `font-display` utility), body font: `Inter`.
- Logo: `public/phc-icon.svg`, `public/phc-logo.svg`.

## Routes

Index `/` redirects to:

1. `/auth` if not signed in,
2. `/onboarding/role` if signed in but no role,
3. `/clipper/dashboard` or `/brand/dashboard` based on role.

The route guard is `src/components/guards/ProtectedRoute.tsx` with props `index`, `guestOnly`, `requireAuth`, and `requiredRole`.

## What this codebase does **not** have

- No HTTP/REST/axios layer (no `src/api/*`).
- No Solana / wallet adapters.
- No Supabase / TanStack Query.
- No real Xendit calls — payouts and invoices are simulated with toasts and store updates.
